  "top10": {
    "introHtml": "<p>Ranked for <strong>cheap fun second-car duty</strong> near Media, PA — prioritizing top condition, model reliability, and driving engagement. All under $15k within 35 miles. Manual preferred but not required. PPI checklist included for every pick.</p>",
    "picks": [
      {
        "rank": 1,
        "year": 2009,
        "make": "Pontiac",
        "model": "Solstice GXP",
        "trim": "Convertible",
        "price": 8195,
        "mileage": 88260,
        "location": "Pennsauken Township, NJ",
        "distance": 18,
        "source": "Cars.com",
        "dealRating": "Great Deal / High Demand",
        "url": "https://www.cars.com/vehicledetail/acecdf65-3af2-4977-8817-48257ce4011b/",
        "whyGood": "The GXP is the turbocharged Solstice (260hp, 2.0L Ecotec) — far more engaging than the base model. The Pontiac Solstice is on the task's reliable model list, 88K miles is excellent for the Kappa platform, Cars.com rates it Great Deal with High Demand, and at 18 miles it's an easy test drive. The Ecotec turbo is factory-reliable when oil is changed regularly.",
        "whatToVerify": "Operate the soft top through a full open/close cycle; listen for motor hesitation. Check headliner and rear-seat carpet for water ingress. Inspect rocker panels for surface rust. Verify oil change history — turbos need clean oil. GXP specific: inspect charge pipe for cracks, confirm boost pull in 2nd gear. Check HVAC (defrost essential for top-down use in PA shoulder seasons).",
        "bottomLine": "Best all-round pick: turbocharged fun, honest mileage, Great Deal + High Demand, 18 miles away."
      },
      {
        "rank": 2,
        "year": 2001,
        "make": "BMW",
        "model": "325 Ci",
        "trim": "Convertible (E46)",
        "price": 10000,
        "mileage": 60200,
        "location": "Norristown, PA",
        "distance": 16,
        "source": "Cars.com",
        "dealRating": "Great Deal",
        "url": "https://www.cars.com/vehicledetail/e3da9c87-515e-4156-a3f5-c97da877c56f/",
        "whyGood": "The E46 325Ci convertible is the most driver-focused affordable BMW cabrio — a proper 4-seater with the silky M54 inline-6 (184hp). Only 60K miles at this price is exceptional; most E46 cabriolets at this budget have 130K+. Great Deal rating, 16 miles away. The M54 is bulletproof when the cooling system is maintained.",
        "whatToVerify": "Top: full open/close cycle, inspect rear window seam for delamination (common on E46 cabrios). Headliner for staining. Engine: coolant expansion tank cracks (known weak spot — plastic tank at rear of engine bay), valve cover oil leaks. Check power window regulators (rear ones fail). Verify no CEL codes. Inspect rear subframe mounting points for cracks (less common at 60K but important on any E46 cabrio).",
        "bottomLine": "Exceptional low-mileage E46 cabriolet — rare to find under 70K miles at this budget."
      },
      {
        "rank": 3,
        "year": 2006,
        "make": "Pontiac",
        "model": "Solstice",
        "trim": "Roadster (base)",
        "price": 7500,
        "mileage": 62995,
        "location": "Telford, PA",
        "distance": 27,
        "source": "CarGurus",
        "dealRating": "Great Deal",
        "url": "https://www.cargurus.com/search?zip=19063&sortType=PRICE&sortDirection=ASC&distance=35&maxPrice=15000&bodyTypeGroupIds=1",
        "whyGood": "Base Solstice with only 63K miles at $7,500 — CarGurus rates it Great Deal. The 2.4L Ecotec is simple and reliable with no turbo complexity. 63K miles is well under the Kappa platform's sweet spot. $700 cheaper than the GXP with even lower miles.",
        "whatToVerify": "Same soft-top checklist as the GXP. Confirm factory or documented service records. Check rocker panels and underbody for rust (PA/NJ road salt). Ensure HVAC and rear defroster work. Test all weather seals.",
        "bottomLine": "Lower mileage than the GXP, Great Deal, $700 cheaper — ideal if you prefer naturally aspirated simplicity."
      },
      {
        "rank": 4,
        "year": 2000,
        "make": "BMW",
        "model": "Z3",
        "trim": "2.8 Roadster",
        "price": 7940,
        "mileage": 75000,
        "location": "~15 mi away",
        "distance": 15,
        "source": "AutoTrader",
        "dealRating": "Private Seller — No Accidents, Clean Title",
